    "The most well-known method for this is Pearson's correlation coefficient, defined as where x and y denote the mean values of the vectors (x 1,.",
    ", x n) and (y 1,.",
    ", y n), respectively 29.",
    "However, Pear- son's correlation coefficient is designed for measuring correlation between variables whose marginal distributions are assumed to be normal.",
    "Because of this, Spearman's correlation coefficient r s might be a better evaluation metric when the real values x i are not even approximately normally distributed."
  ]
}